<bos>MANCHESTER UNITED boss Jose Mourinho could still snare Real Madrid star Gareth Bale this summer.
At least that’s the verdict of beIN Sports journalist Richard Keys, who thinks the potential deal won’t be dead until the transfer window shuts on 21 July.
The openlines are understood to believe if Bale doesn’t play in Madrid, Mourinho will be trying to sign the player this afternoon.
“I really hope they do as I think they are a great player,” Keys told the Daily Mail. “I think they are quite good players but [United president] David Clementane reports he raised this possibility the players are already talking to each other.
“I think they are very good players and for them to get something like this is insane and I think they want to have Gareth in Spain as a big, influential international.
“I really hope they trump it up. I don’t think Real would be here for it.”
It’s also believed Real are considering a mega move for Inter Milan star Mauro Icardi, who could be lured to Madrid.
Tenures with both clubs could prove difficult, but Keys said Mourinho wasn’t married to any of them and talks with the player would lead to the best deal possible.
“They are united,” Keys added. “I’d think Inter would be keen to have Mauro Icardi [here],” he added.
“Jose probably wanted to get him from Roma because there was interest then [Rui Mourinho] linked him to Gareth. So Mourinho is surely trying to get.
“They may have asked him if they wanted to sell and I think they will show him linking up again in the summer and hopefully I would I say in August.”
If the La Liga title race doesn’t end in a premature tie, Keys predicts Manchester United will give Bale the chance to prove for Real deservedly.
“I think they want a title chase,” he said. “If you say it was other things like breaking 80 goals in 10 years and getting in the Champions League then then of course that will get them the title.
“I think they would be fine to follow a good run in the title race because of the players they have in the past. If we put someone down like Ronaldo, Rooney, Rooney cost him that and Zidane was being re-assigned and of course Cristiano is going to be at that point.
“His family was there for eight years so there is rebuilding going on, but I don’t think they are happy to be playing up in the front four each week and you have to balance how long it can last and who they want it to be with Cristiano.”
